    <description>Believe me, you don't want a feed spell! And it won't help your issue with the class. Giving you something other to do isn't going to fix the class. And your core issue afaik is that you can't mitigate initial spike dps enough to recover from a bad pull. Resists do play a role but they wouldn't be that critical if you infact had a way to stand up to a few adds and be able to lock them down. So if you can think of a way to reduce spike dps for the first few seconds without enabling you to tank mobs go for it. Like a manashield that shields against damage at a steadily increasing mana cost for example.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;But don't ask for feed. It's for a reason this spell is loathed by quite a few necros. ;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Oh and I'd love to get the illusions back the way they were - with full faction adjustments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sathras&lt;br&gt;70 necro&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
