      <title>Re: What Enchanters Really Need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6194#M6194</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Its been almost 10 months since I originally made this post and of all the suggestions I had made only a very few came to light.When this post was made the resist issue was a hot topic and it was and still is ignored.We are the red headed step child of classes in EQ in that we are noticed but quickly ignored and forgotten because the bulk of the eq community plays other classes such as clerics,warriors,bards,and necros.Nanyea posted that a survey was done and SOE found that enchanters were something like #3 ranked on number of classes in game,yet,an amazing number of those were below 70.She also commented about the large number of lvl 70 chanters that have quit and sold their accounts.On my server there are several high end raiding guild who regularly farm areas like DoN,DoD,GoD end zones,and of course Anguish.The majority of those guilds bought the accounts of the enchanters who were once loyal members,specifically so they would not lose a BUFFBOT for raids.The remaining enchanters here are hardheads who continue to hope for a return to our previous usefulness,our ability to control mobs and a situation when it arises.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Since this post was made no more "Reinvisionment" has been made,nor has it been mentioned.Instead we are handed yet again a few paltry spells hoping that we will not raise a stink about how gimp we have become,or about how the other rival classes such as bards and necros have been given more of the abilities we should have gotten,and how they have become more useful on raids and in groups while we have become more useless.God forbid someone brings up the suggestion of an enchanter "sit-down" or strike like the Warriors did a couple years back because SOE is already trying its best to do away with this class altogether.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Nanyea I respect the amount of time and effort you are doing for us,but new spells at this point is not the answer.SOE needs to stop dead in the water and stop with the expansions for a year or more,and they need to do it now.We need to have the reinvisionment completed,our class more defined,overhauled,and put back in its proper prespective.We need the abilities that we have been asking about for almost 3-4 years to be granted and our class be made more survivable in any situation.Mezz resists are a freakin joke,as are the mobs who need to be tashed and hit with Desolate Deeds 6-8 times before they are slowed.At lvl 70,with 11k hp and mana,I shouldnt have to hit a mob repeatedly 6-8 times with the same spell to get an effect.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We should not have to invest time into grinding aa's or doing a "bust ass" quest for a spell that will help regen only a SMALL amount of mana and take up another buff slot.This group mana regen should be made an inherent ability of grouping with an enchanter,based upon the level of the enchanter from the time he/she starts at level 1 all the way to lvl 70.This inherent regen would&amp;nbsp;stack with &amp;nbsp;the enchanters own regen spells also,solving yet another ability many have asked for in the form of a self only regen buff.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Enchanters are supposed to be the "Masters of the Mind" and it's workings,giving us the ability to help our own and others minds regen and gather mana at a faster rate,and the ability to control minds,forcing one to do our bidding against its will.With this in mind how the hell did Necromancers get the ability to feed MANA to another class?Hit points I can see,they control the dead,death,and have a better understanding of the body and its workings,but not the mind.I made a suggetion on another post a year ago about giving us that ability and someone mentioned that would give guilds the excuse to DC enchanters on raids to do nothing more than&amp;nbsp;feed &amp;nbsp;clerics...........NEWSFLASH - enchanters are DCed on raids now to BUFF.Giving us the ability to feed mana would give us a more useful role on raids especially if this ability overwrote a necros and was superior to theirs.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The basics that we have all asked for have and continue to be overlooked,that mainly being lower resists on mobs so our debuffs and charms stick,and our survivability.We as a class do not possess the healing spells and abilities of other classes who have similar abilities to ours,yet we are the ones who suffer.Hell we dont even have a pet heal spell yet are given an animation who is one rounded by any mob in the high end spectrum.And in case the devs forgot this little tidbit of info - we were given Gimpy Mcstab as a "pet" because we HAD the ability to charm.Charm was the obvious alternative to using a crappy pet,a pet that isnt even controlable unless we grind more aa's and time into purchasing commands to make it run and hide before it is one rounded.Charm was an integral part of this class to make it on par with the other classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The devs need to think this one through long and hard - when they hear about Shamans,Necros,Bards,Wizzies,Mages,and Shadow Knights soloing mobs like Tallon and Vallon Zek in the planes,they should notice Enchanters are not&amp;nbsp;included on that list.Many of us dont want to be either,we just want the ability to solo viably&amp;nbsp;and &amp;nbsp;get experiance when we cant find groups.We are dieing as a class,being made into more upgraded buffbots,and all because of them.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
