      <title>Re: What Enchanters Really Need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=4643#M4643</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Excellent set of suggestions.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The keys to making enchanters fun to play again:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;SURVIVABILITY.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Our job is to get initial aggro on a mob and stop it.&amp;nbsp; We need to be able to survive long enough to do that.&amp;nbsp; However you do it . . . improved runes or Mind over Mana, inproved damage avoidance or mitigation.&amp;nbsp; Stuns that cast fast enough and land reliably enough to stop a mob long enough for a lock-down.&amp;nbsp; We need to be able to do our jobs and not splat.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;EFFECTIVENESS:&amp;nbsp; Our spells need to actually work.&amp;nbsp; This means lowering the insane magic resistance of mobs that require 3 or 4 casts of a spell for it to land.&amp;nbsp; This means getting rid of the gaps that force enchanters to play in zones with no tools that work (getting rid of the hard level caps on mezzes and stuns and letting them scale they way our nukes do in harder content.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Right now we are not able to perform any of the basic functions of our class.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We can't crowd control because we die every time a mez is resisted.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We can't charm because the laughable damage our pets do is not worth the risk, and groups/raids won't tolerate them.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Many class-defining abilities such as illusions are obsolete and have not been used seriously in play for years.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We are third rate or worse&amp;nbsp;compared to&amp;nbsp;other classes in all&amp;nbsp;the things we CAN do: slow, haste, nuke.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The suggestions above would address these issues.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
