    <item>
      <title>Re: What Enchanters Really Need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=4644#M4644</link>
      <description>I disagree with your nuke claim.  Enchanters should be doing DPS via a viable charm spell.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mez and Stun aggro is about the same.  Stuns have their own problems with balancing.  I'd be happy with either a L 73 cap WoM or a stun that drops a recourse "cannot be PBAOE stunned" for 12 seconds on the mob.  However, PBAOE defences cannot decay to nothing on XP mobs, like they do at L 71 now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The problem with mez resists is not that they happen, but that they are a death sentance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Start mitigating resist modifiers on mobs.  You should be able to design a system so that new spells penetrate resist mitigation better but don't work better on old mobs, thereby fixing the resist-spiral-out-of-control problem.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't want to be able to feed mana to other classes.  It's a cute idea, but it isn't an interesting job.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't want more buffs.  Enchanters are, on the aggregate, a pretty strong buff class.  More buffs means more power allocated to passive abilities.  I don't want to be an afk-bot class, nor do I want to be overpowered.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bards breaking the haste cap is an active way they can add a DPS contribution.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Making enchanters more durable is good.  However, we don't want to revamp itemization.  I would propose making them more durable via spells and innate abilities, rather than gear, is best.  It should also scale with gear.  I don't think druid is enough: we need short-term durability on the level of a full tank, but we also need to be worse than tanks at long-term durability.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I'm disagreeing with you simply because lack of disagreement can cause SOE to confuse apathy with agreement.  We don't need fixes in many of the areas where you want changes, and I want SOE to work on things that will actually fix the class.</description>
